pageContext.claim: “Ohio just had the best year, economically, in the history of your state.”
pageContext.analysis: This is false. "If you're looking at job growth, it likely wasn't Ohio's best year. December job numbers aren't out yet, but year-over-year growth through November was minuscule: 0.4% according to U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics numbers. That’s the lowest rate in the last 10 years," said the Cincinnati Enquirer. "The state was on track for a net job loss in 2019 for the first time since the recession. The preliminary November jobs report showed 4,400 fewer private jobs than in January."
